parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The frame is severely corroded
rusted
or rotten
with holes or chunks of metal falling off; the vehicle shakes or squeaks while driving; the gas tank shield has fallen off; the rear stabilizer bar and bracket have detached from the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame can lead to a loss of structural integrity, causing the vehicle to break apart while in motion, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame
especially in the rear suspension area
loud noises or vibrations while driving
and sudden loss of control or swerving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of control or swerving
loud noises or vibrations while driving
and rust or corrosion on the rear suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal drops to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
a loud grinding or rumbling noise is heard when braking
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle accelerates forward when the brakes are applied
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
a loud grinding or rumbling noise is heard when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust is visible on the frame of the vehicle
the vehicle is deemed unsafe to drive by a mechanic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and engine can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle's lights or accessories do not function properly.
